Figured out a way to do this a little differently.  Essentially instead of worrying about naming the backup table to start, I just rename it after it successfully is populated with the data snapshot.

    create table backup like ops_weekly_sla;

    INSERT INTO backup
    select * from ops_weekly_sla;

    SET @yyyymmdd = DATE_FORMAT(NOW(), &#39;%Y%m%d%H%i&#39;);
    SET @a = concat(&#39;RENAME TABLE `backup` to `ops_weekly_sla.&#39;,@yyyymmdd,&#39;.backup`;&#39;);

    PREPARE stmt from @a;
    EXECUTE stmt;
    DEALLOCATE PREPARE stmt;

Not only did this achieve my goal, bonus feature was that it did not disturb my timestamps for original data insertion or row updates.  /wewt!

